Key Match Events: Damian Lillard scored 34 points to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 123-100 victory over the Utah Jazz.
Giannis Antetokounmpo added 31 points and 16 rebounds.
Bobby Portis contributed 19 points off the bench.
The Bucks outscored the Jazz 31-16 in the third quarter to take a decisive lead.
Post-Match Reflections: Damian Lillard expressed relief and optimism after the win, stating the team needs to use this momentum going forward.
